properties.otherAdvice:
Temporary traffic changes around the University of Wollongong and TAFE NSW will be in place from Monday 26 February 2024 for approximately six weeks, to minimise congestion for the start of the university year. 

The temporary traffic changes are as follows:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout, between 7.45am and 9.15am on weekdays. 
  • If congestion is observed on Irvine Street the Western Entry detour will be implemented, traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted to the University Western Access route via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road during peak periods.  
  • Motorists accessing the M1 northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Avenue during peak periods will be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road.  

Bus access from University Avenue into Irvine Street will not be affected during diversions and outside peak periods traffic will continue to access the University via Irvine Street and Northfields Avenue.

Special event clearways will be in place continuously from 2am Sat 2 Mar to 2am Mon 4 Mar 2024 at the following locations to facilitate rail replacement bus operations for Metro North West trackwork:

  • Railway St, southbound between Day St and Help St,
  • Railway St, northbound between Help St and Brown St, and
  • Brown St, westbound between Railway St and Pacific Hwy.

No-stopping zones will also be in place northbound on Railway St between Brown St and Help St during this time.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones for all vehicle types, and apply even to local residents and businesses with parking permits or TfNSW Mobility Scheme permit holders. If your vehicle is towed, you can search your vehicle registration at the Find My Car website to find its new location, or alternatively call 132 701 to speak to an operator.
